WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.450 --> 00:00:03.660
Prof: All right,
welcome back.

00:00:03.660 --> 00:00:07.360
We're going to do a brand new
topic.

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:09.722
Well actually,
a brand old topic,

00:00:09.722 --> 00:00:14.288
because it's about light,
but I'm going to go backwards

00:00:14.288 --> 00:00:18.212
in time,
because just before the break,

00:00:18.212 --> 00:00:21.990
we had this finish with a
flourish,

00:00:21.990 --> 00:00:24.300
Maxwell's theory of light.
 

00:00:24.300 --> 00:00:28.569
We took Ampere's law and Lenz's
law and Faraday's law and all

00:00:28.569 --> 00:00:32.151
kinds of stuff,
put them together and out came

00:00:32.151 --> 00:00:36.295
the news: the view that
electromagnetic waves can exist

00:00:36.295 --> 00:00:39.501
on their own,
travel away from charges and

00:00:39.501 --> 00:00:40.180
currents.
 

00:00:40.180 --> 00:00:43.304
And they travel at a speed
which happened to coincide with

00:00:43.304 --> 00:00:45.890
the speed of light,
and people conjectured,

00:00:45.890 --> 00:00:48.326
quite correctly,
that light was an

00:00:48.326 --> 00:00:50.560
electromagnetic phenomenon.
 

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:53.990
And it was an oscillatory
phenomenon,

00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:58.941
but what's oscillating is not a
piece of wire or some water on a

00:00:58.941 --> 00:01:01.412
lake,
but what's oscillating is the

00:01:01.412 --> 00:01:02.429
electric field.
 

00:01:02.429 --> 00:01:03.929
It's oscillating in strength.
 

00:01:03.929 --> 00:01:06.069
The field is not jumping up and
down.

00:01:06.069 --> 00:01:08.280
The field is a condition at a
certain point,

00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:11.569
you sit at a certain point,
sometimes the field points up,

00:01:11.569 --> 00:01:13.280
sometimes the field points
down, it's strong,

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:16.390
it's weak, and you can measure
it by putting a test charge.

00:01:16.390 --> 00:01:21.489
It's that condition in space
that travels from source to some

00:01:21.489 --> 00:01:22.680
other place.
 

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:27.983
Now that point of view came
near the second half of the

00:01:27.983 --> 00:01:32.108
nineteenth century,
and it came after many,

00:01:32.108 --> 00:01:35.349
many years of studying light.
 

00:01:35.349 --> 00:01:39.816
And what I'm going to do is to
tell you two different ways in

00:01:39.816 --> 00:01:43.241
which you can go away from the
theory of light,

00:01:43.241 --> 00:01:45.400
of electromagnetic waves.
 

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:53.358
One is, when the wavelength of
light is much smaller than your

00:01:53.358 --> 00:01:57.646
scale of observation,
namely, you're looking at a

00:01:57.646 --> 00:02:00.129
situation where you're thinking
in terms of centimeters and

00:02:00.129 --> 00:02:03.221
meters and so on,
and the wavelength of light is

00:02:03.221 --> 00:02:07.656
10^(-8) centimeters,
then light behaves in a much

00:02:07.656 --> 00:02:08.968
simpler way.
 

00:02:08.968 --> 00:02:12.955
You can forget about the waves,
then you get this theory of

00:02:12.955 --> 00:02:17.008
light in which you have what's
called geometrical optics.

00:02:17.008 --> 00:02:21.699
Geometrical optics is just
light going in a straight line

00:02:21.699 --> 00:02:25.720
from start to finish,
from source to your eye.

00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:29.669
So if you take Maxwell theory
and apply it to a situation

00:02:29.669 --> 00:02:32.348
where the wavelength is very
small,

00:02:32.348 --> 00:02:35.556
then you get this approximation
that I'm going to discuss for a

00:02:35.556 --> 00:02:36.280
while today.
 

00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:38.627
But when you say very small,
you always have to ask,

00:02:38.627 --> 00:02:40.330
"Small compared to
what?"

00:02:40.330 --> 00:02:41.310
Do you understand that?
 

00:02:41.310 --> 00:02:44.614
When someone says wavelength is
small, as it is,

00:02:44.614 --> 00:02:46.020
it has no meaning.
 

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:48.917
I can pick units in which the
wavelength is million or 1

00:02:48.917 --> 00:02:49.550
millionth.
 

00:02:49.550 --> 00:02:50.699
That has no meaning.
 

00:02:50.699 --> 00:02:53.250
Small and large can be changed
by change of units.

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:57.696
What we really mean is the
following: suppose I have a

00:02:57.696 --> 00:03:01.218
screen and there's a hole in the
screen.

00:03:01.218 --> 00:03:04.508
And behind the screen,
there is a source of light.

00:03:04.508 --> 00:03:10.043
Then I put another screen here
and the light goes through that

00:03:10.043 --> 00:03:15.758
and forms an image which you can
obtain just by drawing straight

00:03:15.758 --> 00:03:18.568
lines from start to finish.
 

00:03:18.568 --> 00:03:24.293
So you illuminate a region
which is the same shape as what

00:03:24.293 --> 00:03:25.800
you had here.
 

00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:29.378
That's what makes people think
of using ray optics.

00:03:29.378 --> 00:03:31.520
Ray optics, the light rays come
out,

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.810
they're blocked by the screen
except near the hole,

00:03:33.810 --> 00:03:37.074
except inside the hole,
and the light escapes through

00:03:37.074 --> 00:03:40.970
that hole and fans out and forms
an image of the same shape.

00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:45.197
If you made a blip here in the
hole, you'll get a blip in the

00:03:45.197 --> 00:03:48.650
image, because it will simply
follow the shape.

00:03:48.650 --> 00:03:52.223
Now I can tell you what I mean
by, the wavelength is small or

00:03:52.223 --> 00:03:52.699
large.
 

00:03:52.699 --> 00:03:56.170
It's going to be small or large
compared to the size of this

00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:56.758
opening.
 

00:03:56.758 --> 00:03:59.139
If λ,
the wavelength,

00:03:59.139 --> 00:04:03.723
is much less than d,
which is the size of that

00:04:03.723 --> 00:04:07.162
opening here,
then you have this simpler

00:04:07.162 --> 00:04:09.189
geometric optics.
 

00:04:09.189 --> 00:04:15.330
That's the approximation.
 

00:04:15.330 --> 00:04:17.877
It's like saying,
if you have understood

00:04:17.877 --> 00:04:20.360
Einstein's relativistic
kinematics,

00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:22.750
if you go to small
velocities--again,

00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:24.166
one must say,
"Small compared to

00:04:24.166 --> 00:04:24.680
what?"
 

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.040
The answer is small compared to
the speed of light--

00:04:27.040 --> 00:04:29.197
you get another kind of
mechanics called Newtonian

00:04:29.197 --> 00:04:31.471
mechanics,
which is simpler and was

00:04:31.471 --> 00:04:32.750
discovered first.
 

00:04:32.750 --> 00:04:36.173
Likewise, geometrical optics is
simpler than the real thing and

00:04:36.173 --> 00:04:37.720
it was discovered earlier.
 

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:42.403
You will note that this picture
is incomplete if λ

00:04:42.403 --> 00:04:46.250
becomes comparable to the size
of that hole.

00:04:46.250 --> 00:04:50.379
Then you will find out that if
you put a very tiny hole in a

00:04:50.379 --> 00:04:52.165
screen,
and it would be very tiny

00:04:52.165 --> 00:04:55.805
compared to wavelength,
the waves have then spread out

00:04:55.805 --> 00:05:00.920
and formed something much bigger
than the geometric shadow.

00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:03.343
Then you will have to realize
that drawing straight lines

00:05:03.343 --> 00:05:03.949
won't do it.
 

00:05:03.949 --> 00:05:07.399
In other words,
if I show you a side view,

00:05:07.399 --> 00:05:10.778
you would think,
if you had a source,

00:05:10.778 --> 00:05:13.720
you'll form an image of that
dimension on the screen,

00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:17.110
but actually it will spread out
much more.

00:05:17.110 --> 00:05:19.574
And the smaller the hole,
the more the light will fan

00:05:19.574 --> 00:05:19.860
out.
 

00:05:19.860 --> 00:05:23.889
You're not going to get that
from geometrical optics.

00:05:23.889 --> 00:05:26.596
But in order to realize that,
you will have to deal with

00:05:26.596 --> 00:05:29.548
apertures small comparable to
the wavelength of light and the

00:05:29.548 --> 00:05:32.060
wavelength of visible light is
5,000 angstrom,

00:05:32.060 --> 00:05:33.269
which is very small.
 

00:05:33.269 --> 00:05:36.420
So it wasn't known for a while.
 

00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:39.319
Now you might say,
okay, if you want,

00:05:39.319 --> 00:05:42.896
you can go back in time,
but you should probably start

00:05:42.896 --> 00:05:46.810
with this and build your way to
electromagnetic theory a la

00:05:46.810 --> 00:05:47.620
Maxwell.
 

00:05:47.620 --> 00:05:50.675
Well, it turns out Maxwell
isn't right either,

00:05:50.675 --> 00:05:53.322
and to see where Maxwell's
theory fails,

00:05:53.322 --> 00:05:56.990
you will have to take light of
very low intensity.

00:05:56.990 --> 00:05:59.745
Remember, intensity is the
square of the electric field,

00:05:59.745 --> 00:06:00.949
or the magnetic field.
 

00:06:00.949 --> 00:06:02.639
They're all proportional.
 

00:06:02.639 --> 00:06:05.882
If light becomes really dim,
you might think the electric

00:06:05.882 --> 00:06:08.430
field is going to be smaller and
smaller,

00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:10.771
because E^(2) or
B^(2) is a measure of

00:06:10.771 --> 00:06:13.598
intensity,
but something else happens when

00:06:13.598 --> 00:06:15.540
light becomes really week.
 

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:18.629
You realize that the light
energy is not coming to you

00:06:18.629 --> 00:06:22.009
continuously like a wave would,
but in discrete packets.

00:06:22.009 --> 00:06:24.649
These are called photons.
 

00:06:24.649 --> 00:06:27.418
But you won't be aware of
photons if the light is very

00:06:27.418 --> 00:06:30.500
intense, because there are so
many of them coming at you.

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:32.545
It's like saying,
if you look at water waves,

00:06:32.545 --> 00:06:34.870
you see this nice surface and
you're looking at the

00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:36.870
description of that surface
undulating.

00:06:36.870 --> 00:06:38.819
You have a wave equation for
that.

00:06:38.819 --> 00:06:41.425
But if you really look deep
down, it's made of water

00:06:41.425 --> 00:06:44.490
molecules, but you don't see
them and you don't need that for

00:06:44.490 --> 00:06:45.870
describing ocean waves.
 

00:06:45.870 --> 00:06:49.569
But on some deeper level,
water is not a continuous body.

00:06:49.569 --> 00:06:50.949
It's discrete,
made of molecules.

00:06:50.949 --> 00:06:52.879
Likewise, light is not
continuous.

00:06:52.879 --> 00:06:56.970
It's made up of little
particles called photons.

00:06:56.970 --> 00:06:59.089
And that we will talk about
later.

00:06:59.089 --> 00:07:01.040
So you understand the picture
now?

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:04.882
You're going back in time to
the ancient theory of light,

00:07:04.882 --> 00:07:06.528
then we did Maxwell's.
 

00:07:06.528 --> 00:07:08.680
I won't stop there,
because I have already done it,

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:10.810
and we'll go onto the new
theory of light,

00:07:10.810 --> 00:07:13.285
which involves photons,
and that's part of what's

00:07:13.285 --> 00:07:17.687
called quantum mechanics,
so we'll certainly talk about

00:07:17.687 --> 00:07:18.300
that.
 

00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:20.610
So what did people know about
light?

00:07:20.610 --> 00:07:24.120
Well, they had an intuitive
feeling that something bright or

00:07:24.120 --> 00:07:26.740
shiny emits some light and you
can see it.

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:29.555
It seemed to travel in a
straight line,

00:07:29.555 --> 00:07:33.706
and for the longest time,
people did not know how fast it

00:07:33.706 --> 00:07:34.670
traveled.
 

00:07:34.670 --> 00:07:37.007
It looked like it traveled
instantaneously,

00:07:37.007 --> 00:07:40.069
because you couldn't measure
the delay of light in daily

00:07:40.069 --> 00:07:40.569
life.
 

00:07:40.569 --> 00:07:43.939
You can measure the delay of
sound, but not the delay of

00:07:43.939 --> 00:07:44.430
light.
 

00:07:44.430 --> 00:07:46.689
They knew it travels in a
straight line,

00:07:46.689 --> 00:07:48.947
unlike some,
because if I close my face,

00:07:48.947 --> 00:07:51.440
you can hear me,
but you cannot see me.

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:53.735
So sound waves can get around
an obstacle, but not light

00:07:53.735 --> 00:07:54.069
waves.
 

00:07:54.069 --> 00:07:57.019
That one, everybody knew.
 

00:07:57.019 --> 00:07:59.129
But they did not know how fast
it travels.

00:07:59.129 --> 00:08:01.125
Sound, they knew,
travels at a finite speed,

00:08:01.125 --> 00:08:03.629
because you go to the mountain
and start yelling at the

00:08:03.629 --> 00:08:04.930
mountain, it yells back.
 

00:08:04.930 --> 00:08:08.990
You can even time it and find
the velocity of sound.

00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:13.329
So Galileo tried to find the
velocity of light by asking one

00:08:13.329 --> 00:08:17.230
of his buddies to go stand on
top of one mountain,

00:08:17.230 --> 00:08:21.009
and he's going to stand on top
of the other mountain with a

00:08:21.009 --> 00:08:22.769
lantern which is blocked.
 

00:08:22.769 --> 00:08:25.473
Then he's going to open the
lantern and the minute his

00:08:25.473 --> 00:08:28.415
friend saw this light,
he was supposed to signal back

00:08:28.415 --> 00:08:31.069
with another light signal,
come back to Galileo.

00:08:31.069 --> 00:08:33.788
Meanwhile, he was timing it
with his pulse.

00:08:33.788 --> 00:08:38.200
Then he was going to--well,
that's the only clock you had

00:08:38.200 --> 00:08:39.460
in those days.
 

00:08:39.460 --> 00:08:42.506
I think the two mountains were
like 20 miles apart or

00:08:42.506 --> 00:08:45.614
something, so it's not
impossible that with the pulse,

00:08:45.614 --> 00:08:47.899
you can probably find the
velocity.

00:08:47.899 --> 00:08:51.384
So you've got some answer,
but I think he realized very

00:08:51.384 --> 00:08:55.125
quickly that that answer just
measured the reaction time of

00:08:55.125 --> 00:08:56.610
him and his friend.
 

00:08:56.610 --> 00:08:58.961
Do you know how you will
realize that,

00:08:58.961 --> 00:09:02.710
that it's the reaction time and
not the propagation time?

00:09:02.710 --> 00:09:04.580
How will you find out?
 

00:09:04.580 --> 00:09:06.190
You all had a good laugh at
Mr. G.

00:09:06.190 --> 00:09:08.139
but what will you do?
 

00:09:08.139 --> 00:09:10.418
How will you know that it's
really--yes?

00:09:10.418 --> 00:09:11.620
Student:  Vary the
distance between them.

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:12.500
Prof: You vary the
distance.

00:09:12.500 --> 00:09:13.820
If he and his friend,
instead of being on two

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:15.688
different mountains,
are in the same room,

00:09:15.688 --> 00:09:18.889
and they do the experiment and
they get the same delay,

00:09:18.889 --> 00:09:21.000
then they know that it's
nothing to do with the travel

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:21.278
time.
 

00:09:21.278 --> 00:09:24.798
It's just how long it takes
them to react.

00:09:24.798 --> 00:09:28.288
So the real serious measurement
of light,

00:09:28.288 --> 00:09:30.287
you can't ask yourself,
"How am I going to measure

00:09:30.287 --> 00:09:31.730
it if it's traveling that
fast?"

00:09:31.730 --> 00:09:34.426
First of all,
you don't even know if it takes

00:09:34.426 --> 00:09:35.529
any finite time.
 

00:09:35.529 --> 00:09:38.261
It's possible to imagine that
if you turn something on,

00:09:38.261 --> 00:09:39.679
you can see it right away.
 

00:09:39.679 --> 00:09:41.259
It looks very natural.
 

00:09:41.259 --> 00:09:45.081
So the fact that it could take
a finite time was a hypothesis,

00:09:45.081 --> 00:09:47.712
but to measure it,
if it's going very fast,

00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:49.529
you need a long distance.
 

00:09:49.529 --> 00:09:52.221
Even the distance equal to the
circumference of the earth is

00:09:52.221 --> 00:09:54.375
not enough,
because it takes one seventh of

00:09:54.375 --> 00:09:56.970
a second for a light signal to
go around the earth,

00:09:56.970 --> 00:10:00.100
if it could be made to go in a
circle.

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:01.639
So that's too fast.
 

00:10:01.639 --> 00:10:06.611
So the idea of finding the
velocity of light,

00:10:06.611 --> 00:10:11.019
the first correct way,
came from Roemer,

00:10:11.019 --> 00:10:13.278
I think in 1676.
 

00:10:13.278 --> 00:10:17.282
He did the following very
clever experiment:

00:10:17.282 --> 00:10:21.096
here's the sun,
let's say, and here is the

00:10:21.096 --> 00:10:23.889
earth and here is Jupiter.
 

00:10:23.889 --> 00:10:27.320
It's got one of these moons
called Io.

00:10:27.320 --> 00:10:30.032
And the moon goes round and
round Jupiter,

00:10:30.032 --> 00:10:33.671
and we know from Newtonian
physics that it will go in an

00:10:33.671 --> 00:10:36.120
orbit with a certain time
period.

00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:39.808
If the earth was stationary,
this would go round and round

00:10:39.808 --> 00:10:41.038
with some period.
 

00:10:41.038 --> 00:10:44.455
I've forgot what it is,
an hour and something,

00:10:44.455 --> 00:10:46.580
to go once around Jupiter.
 

00:10:46.580 --> 00:10:49.490
So what you do is you record
the pulse.

00:10:49.490 --> 00:10:52.106
Let's say you wait until it's
hidden behind Jupiter,

00:10:52.106 --> 00:10:54.158
or it comes right in front of
Jupiter.

00:10:54.158 --> 00:10:57.568
Pick any one key event in its
orbit, then wait for the next

00:10:57.568 --> 00:11:00.861
pulse, and wait for the next
pulse, and wait for the next

00:11:00.861 --> 00:11:01.450
pulse.
 

00:11:01.450 --> 00:11:03.009
You understand what I mean by
pulse?

00:11:03.009 --> 00:11:06.211
You can see it all the time,
but wait till it comes to a

00:11:06.211 --> 00:11:08.832
particular location in its
orbit, then repeat,

00:11:08.832 --> 00:11:09.940
then time them.
 

00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:12.110
So that should be one hour and
something.

00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:15.450
Let's say one hour exactly.
 

00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:20.423
But you notice that as the
earth begins its journey around

00:11:20.423 --> 00:11:24.436
the sun, it takes longer and
longer and longer,

00:11:24.436 --> 00:11:28.450
the pulses get spaced apart a
little more.

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:32.203
And he found out that if you go
to this situation when the earth

00:11:32.203 --> 00:11:34.832
is here,
Jupiter hasn't moved very much

00:11:34.832 --> 00:11:40.538
in this time,
it takes about 22 minutes more.

00:11:40.538 --> 00:11:44.764
Namely, this pulse,
with respect to the anticipated

00:11:44.764 --> 00:11:47.299
time, is 22 minutes delayed.
 

00:11:47.299 --> 00:11:47.779
Do you understand?
 

00:11:47.779 --> 00:11:51.812
The delay is continuous,
but take the case now and take

00:11:51.812 --> 00:11:55.658
the case six months later,
and the pulse should have come

00:11:55.658 --> 00:11:57.620
right there if it was not
moving,

00:11:57.620 --> 00:12:01.230
but it comes 22 minutes later.
 

00:12:01.230 --> 00:12:05.722
And he attributed that to the
fact that it takes light time to

00:12:05.722 --> 00:12:08.393
travel,
and it takes an extra time of

00:12:08.393 --> 00:12:12.259
traveling the whole diameter of
the orbit around the sun.

00:12:12.259 --> 00:12:15.528
And that's the 22 minutes.
 

00:12:15.528 --> 00:12:16.899
And how do you know you are
right?

00:12:16.899 --> 00:12:20.690
Well, you know you are right,
because as you start going back

00:12:20.690 --> 00:12:24.164
now, the remaining six months,
the pulses get closer and

00:12:24.164 --> 00:12:24.860
closer.
 

00:12:24.860 --> 00:12:26.559
So this delay is clearly due to
